# 1. いつものお返しに

Shizuku: Thank you for tutoring me today, Asahina. I was absent for this class due to work, so you really saved me.
Mafuyu: You're welcome. I was also thinking about reviewing the same material, so it was a win-win for the both of us.
Mafuyu: Speaking of work, Hinomori, everyone in my class has been talking about your commercial. I was honestly staggered when I saw how beautiful you looked.
Shizuku: Oh, you saw it? Thank you.
Shizuku: But I can't rest on my laurels. I need to make the most of my success by continuing to do my best.
Mafuyu: Hehe. You're such a hard-working girl.
Mafuyu: You have my support, so please feel free to ask me for help whenever you need it.
Shizuku: Asahina...
Shizuku: (She's such a kind person...)
Shizuku: (Even the other day, she agreed to do my share of the cleaning after I had to leave early...)
Shizuku: (She's been providing me with so much support.)
Shizuku: (If only there were a way for me to thank her...)
Mafuyu: H-Hinomori, watch out!
Shizuku: Huh?
Shizuku: Eep...!
Mafuyu: I'm sorry for yanking you so suddenly, but that pile of snow was about to fall on top of you.
Shizuku: No, I really appreciate it. You kept me from getting all wet.
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: There's some snow on your shoulder, Asahina.
Mafuyu: Huh? Oh, you're right...
Shizuku: Just give me a second to get it with my handkerchief.
Shizuku: Okay, that's all of it.
Mafuyu: Thank you.
Mafuyu: Oh, your handkerchief... The embroidery on it is beautiful. Are these camellias?
Shizuku: Yes, I saw one blooming in my garden, so I decided to make an embroidery of it.
Mafuyu: Wait, you did this yourself?
Mafuyu: I remember saying how beautiful that other embroidery you showed me the other day was. It's incredible how you're able to create these intricate designs.
Shizuku: Thank you. But it's actually not as difficult as all that.
Shizuku: For example, these camellias use only stitches taught in home ec.
Mafuyu: Really?
Shizuku: Yes, for instance... I made the stems using back stitches, and the anthers on the stamens using French knots.
Mafuyu: Interesting. I thought there were much more complicated stitches involved...
Mafuyu: I saw some girls doing embroidery for their home ec projects. I might just do the same now.
Shizuku: What project?
Mafuyu: Oh, that's right. You're not taking home ec this term, are you?
Mafuyu: We were recently asked to make some accessories of our choice as part of a project. That includes pen cases, pouches and such...
Mafuyu: We can apparently score bonus points by sewing on buttons and embroidering them.
Shizuku: I see. Which is why some girls are choosing to embroider theirs...
Shizuku: Getting to design your project however you like sounds like so much fun! What do you plan on doing for yours, Asahina?
Mafuyu: I'm going make a tissue box cover. I found some instructions in the supply catalog, so I'll be following that mostly.
Mafuyu: But I still haven't decided how I'm going to decorate it.
Mafuyu: I wish I knew how to embroider like you, Hinomori. I'd have more options if I did.
Shizuku: More options...
Shizuku: Would you like me to teach you?
Mafuyu: Huh?
Shizuku: Oh, I'm sorry. I know this is sudden, and I don't actually know if I'll be able to help...
Shizuku: But you should be able to apply what I teach you to your project, which in turn should make it more fun.
Mafuyu: Hinomori... Thank you.
Mafuyu: I appreciate the offer. But you don't have to do that. I know your work as an idol keeps you very busy...
Shizuku: Don't worry about me. I can teach you a few simple stitches during lunch.
Shizuku: Also...
Shizuku: You've done so much for me in the past, Asahina. It would make me happy to know I could help you too.
Mafuyu: If you're willing to say that, then I might just have to take you up on your offer.
Shizuku: You will? Thank goodness...!
Shizuku: In that case, why don't we meet during lunch tomorrow?
Mafuyu: Yes, that sounds good. I'll be looking forward to our lesson.
Shizuku: Let's see... I have my needles and embroidery hoops, so that just leaves...
Shizuku: Oh, we're going to need some extra cloth and thread to use for practice. I should have some little pieces somewhere...
Shizuku: (Hehe. I'm so glad that I finally get to help Asahina.)
Shizuku: (I have to prepare a good lesson for her.)
???: <Shizuku.>
Shizuku: Huh?
Shizuku: Oh, Len...! Good evening.
Len: <Good evening. Sorry for dropping in on you so suddenly.>
Len: <I wanted to ask you about something... Did I come at a bad time?>
Shizuku: No, you're fine. I was just getting some things together for tomorrow.
Len: <What's happening tomorrow?>
Shizuku: Hehe. I promised a friend that I'd teach her how to embroider during lunch.
Len: <I see. That explains why you have all these sewing supplies out. And this pile of books on embroidery...>
Shizuku: Oh, I'm reading through these again to find some good ideas for my lesson.
Shizuku: That includes deciding which stitches I'm going to teach my friend...
Len: <I see. Sound like you're putting a lot of effort into this.>
Shizuku: Yes... I want to repay her for what she's done for me.
Len: <Repay her?>
Shizuku: I've actually been relying on this friend quite a lot...
Shizuku: Even today, she was kind enough to fill me in on the classes that I missed. It's like she's always there to help...
Shizuku: But this is my chance to help her. That's why I want to give her a proper, good lesson.
Len: <Yeah, it sounds like she means a lot to you.>
Len: <Good luck, Shizuku!>
Shizuku: Yes, thank you!
Shizuku: Oh, I'm sorry... I didn't mean to do all the talking.
Shizuku: You said you wanted to ask me about something, Len?
Len: <Oh, right. For our Valentine's Day, we're thinking about striking poses involving hearts when we talk with the audience and stuff. But I still haven't decided what I'm gonna do...>
Shizuku: Poses involving hearts?
Len: <We're having a contest to see who strikes the best pose that involves hearts.>
Shizuku: Oh, that sounds like a wonderful way to celebrate Valentine's Day! You're all going to look so adorable.
Len: <Yeah, but I wanna try doing a pose that's both cute and stylish.>
Len: <I've been researching expressions and gestures that make me look cool and relaxed... But I felt that I should ask you, Shizuku, since you probably know a lot about this stuff.>
Shizuku: I see. In that case, I'll be more than happy to help.
Len: <Thanks! You're the best. The pose I have in mind right now is...>
